        <ul>
          <li>Keep confidential information private and secure</li>
          <li>Use confidential information only for authorized purposes</li>
          <li>Return or destroy confidential information upon request</li>
          <li>Maintain confidentiality for 3 years after contract termination</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Performance and Results</h2>
        <h3>Best Efforts</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>We will use best efforts to achieve agreed-upon goals</li>
          <li>Results depend on many factors beyond our control</li>
          <li>We do not guarantee specific outcomes or results</li>
          <li>Performance metrics will be tracked and reported regularly</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>External Factors</h3>
        <p>Results may be affected by:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Market conditions and competition</li>
          <li>Platform algorithm changes</li>
          <li>Industry regulations and policies</li>
          <li>Client website and business factors</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Our liability is limited to the fees paid for services</li>
          <li>We are not liable for indirect or consequential damages</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for third-party platform issues</li>
          <li>Clients are responsible for their own business decisions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>Clients agree to indemnify and hold us harmless from claims arising from:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Client's breach of these terms</li>
          <li>Client's violation of laws or regulations</li>
          <li>Client's content or business practices</li>
          <li>Third-party claims related to client's business</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>11. Force Majeure</h2>
        <p>Neither party will be liable for delays or failures due to circumstances beyond reasonable control, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Natural disasters or emergencies</li>
          <li>Government actions or regulations</li>
          <li>Internet or technology failures</li>
          <li>Labor disputes or strikes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>12. Modifications</h2>
        <p>We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be effective upon posting to our website. Continued use of our services constitutes acceptance of modified terms.</p>

        <h2>13. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These terms are governed by the laws of Kenya. Any disputes will be resolved in the courts of Kenya.</p>

